   - `g` as a signed int
   - `h` as a signed int
3. It declares two instances of struct `c` named `i` and `j`.

10. It declares a variable `p` of type `signed int` and assigns the result of the expression `o | -(l.f && l.d) - n` to it.
11. It assigns the value of `p` to `i.g`.
12. The `main` function is defined as an `int` and is empty.
